article.headline: N. Colorado 76, Southern U. 68
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Devon Beitzel scored a game-high 24 points to lead Northern Colorado over Southern 76-68 on Tuesday in the seventh-place game of the Las Vegas Classic. Beitzel was 15-of-16 from the free-throw line. Jabril Banks added 14 points and six rebounds for the Bears (4-8). Teammate Neal Kingman had 12 points and six rebounds, while Will Figures added 11 points. The Bears, who never trailed, used a 13-0 early first-half run and led 39-24 at intermission. Southern got no closer than eight points in the second half. Chris Davis led the Jaguars (0-12) with 15 points and seven rebounds. Earnest Jones added 12 points and five rebounds. Jones was 5-of-5 from the field.
